description: In addition to engraved t.p., 1st part has letterpress t.p.: Sectionis primae portio tertia de Anatomia triplici in partes tres diuisa ... Second part has separate t.p.: Monochordvm mvndi symphoniacvm, seu, Replicatio Roberti Flvd, alias de Flvctibvs ... ad Apologiam viri clariss. et in mathesi peritiss. Ioannis Kepleri, aduersus demonstrationem suam analyticam, nuperrime editam, in qva Robertvs validioribvs Ioannis obiectionibus, harmoniae suae legi repugnantibus, comiter respondere aggreditur. Francofurti : Typis Erasmi Kempferi : Sumptibus Ioan. Theodor. de Bry, anno 1623. Verso of t.p. (1st part) has port. of Johann Theodor de Bry, aged 54, engraved in 1615 apparently by himself. It is accompanied by verses written on the occasion of his death by his son-in-law Iohannes Ammonius Ambergensis. In Library's copy the double-leaf plate after p. 54 is hinged in upside down. Library's copy is bound after v. 2 of: Utriusque cosmi maioris scilicet et minoris metaphysica, physica atque technica historia / Robert Fludd. Oppenhemii : Aere Johan-Theodori de Bry, 1617-1621 (SPECIAL 1378-183 v.2). Pars 1. Hogart, R.C. Alchemy
